# diskcache CVE-2025-69872
# Risk: Attacker with write access to cache directory can execute arbitrary code
# Mitigation: Cache directory is owned by the same user running the application.
# Victor uses diskcache for local caching only, not shared caches.
# Waiting for upstream fix or alternative caching library.
CVE-2025-69872 | diskcache | 5.6.3 | No newer version available. Vulnerability requires attacker write access to cache directory. In Victor's use case, cache directory is owned by application user. Acceptable risk for local caching. Re-evaluate when diskcache 5.7+ is released. | 2025-07-01
